@@CPRIEST@@W

@@CHistory@@W
  The Priest as a formal remort path emerged from the schism within the
  Cleric councils known as the Hour of Quiet Thunder, when a faction of
  senior clerics argued that battlefield ministry had diluted the faith's
  true purpose. These purists withdrew from combat theology and devoted
  themselves entirely to restoration, consecration, and the slow patient work
  of keeping the living alive. They developed healing rites of extraordinary
  sophistication, learned to sustain miracle-channels for hours at a stretch,
  and built the great ward-networks that still shelter pilgrims across the old
  cities. A Priest who has walked back through the mortal disciplines carries
  that reservoir of worldly experience into the sacred work -- they heal not
  from ignorance but from hard-won knowledge of what breaks a body.

Priests are ward-keepers and miracle-callers, trained to outlast chaos through
restoration, sanctification, and relentless holy attrition.

